DDS Analytics… A Passion for Talent

Employee Attrition and Retention Agenda:

  • Business Objectives

  • Data Sourced

  • Methodology

  • Evaluation & Results

  • Summary

Business Objectives Include:

  • Study the attrition rate for all the employees of The Agency.
  • Find out the factors which contributes for the attrition from the data gathered across all Department of The Agency.
  • DDS Analystics will Identify to The Agency the factors which contributed for attrition and provide suggestion to improve employee retention

Points about the Data:

  • Anonymous Data of 1,470 was extracted from The Agency HR System, cleansed, and normalized for analysis.
  • Column headings were reduced to 12 character length due to R Column heading limitations.
  • All Entries contain proper data types used so that when analysis is done, it can differentiate and provide relevant data.

Methodology:

Following is a Methodolgy we used to Analyze and determine the factors which are contributing to the Attrition:

  • Start : We identified what sort of data is given, what different type it is, what is the total size, some basicss about number of columns/rows, and most importantly what is the ask.
  • Plan : Before started coding anything, we planned on the flow of our analysis while coding and tried to use global variables so that those can be used without having to do separate coding for each ask.
  • Deploy : In this phase we made sure we follow our Plan, without having to do ad-hoc coding and clearly state the answers to the questions for our premilinary analysis.
  • Analyze/Optimize : After getting premilinary analysis, we further deep dived in detailed analysis and tried to identified combination of contributing factors for Attrition.
